The class `CanonicalForeignField` does not have a `fromFields` static method, which I believe all provable pure types must implement.

I believe you need to actually create a specific foreign field in order for the type to make sense.  e.g.

```
import {ZkProgram, createForeignField} from 'o1js';

const x = createForeignField(11n);

export const ExampleProgram = ZkProgram({
    name: "exampleCode",
    publicOutput: x.Canonical,

    methods: {
      baseCase: {
        privateInputs: [],

        async method() {
            // Nevermind if this part is correct or not  
          return x.from(3);
        },
      },
    }
}); 
```

